          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "3CPRIMP",
                "3CPRAEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "ACCEL"
                ],
                "institute": "3CPRIMP"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The heavy ion research facility"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The targets used for the irradiation consisted of 99.9%",
                "pure natural niobium and tantalum foils with thickness",
                "of 41.6 and 102 mg/cm2, respectively. Each target was",
                "surrounded by two mylar foils used as forward and",
                "backward recoil catcher foils. Additional mylar foils",
                "served as activation blanks and the whole target",
                "assembly was surrounded by another two mylar foils",
                "which served to guard the assembly from possible",
                "external sources of radioactive products. All the",
                "mylar foils have a thickness of 10.5 mg/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two separate bombardments were done 10 hours in",
                "duration for each, with typical intensities of 5-10",
                "electrical nanoAmperes. The fluencies 7.8E+14 12-C ions",
                "and 2.2E+14 12-C ions for the niobium and tantalum",
                "runs, respectively."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The measurement of gamma-rays began about 30",
                "minutes after the end of irradiation and lasted for",
                "months."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DECAY"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The uncertainties listed in tables are standard",
                "deviation, including errors in the analysis of the",
                "gamma spectra and in the resolution of the decay curves",
                "by the least-squares method, and"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Error in detector efficiencies.",
                " While the uncertainty in the thickness of the targets",
                "was negligible, the uncertainty in beam current",
                "measurement was not taken into account."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "A-DIS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The mass yield distributions were deduced",
                "assuming a Gaussian charge distribution function."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The results were compared with statistical",
                "fusion-fragmentation model calculations."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CRITIQUE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "- By compiler. Decay data for obtained products are",
                "absent in the paper. Therefore identification for some",
                "isomer and ground states are ambiguity. The type of",
                "cross section is ambiguity for some cases too.",
                "Compiler moved some cumulative cross sections to",
                "independent ones for obvious cases. Another cases are",
                "marked by flags and comments."
